{
  "stem": "1965.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 320.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And opposite that was a limousine service.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "All this in one block.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] It was unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And it was very intimate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Life in Belgium was very intimate, small streets.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Everybody knows each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Very provincial.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And my father, who as you know, was very orthodox, he used to go to the shtibl, the shtibl of the [NON-ENGLISH] and the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Both of these men are cousins to my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I would sometimes go to the main synagogue, but not to pray.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I went there to look at boys, because everybody was decked in their finest, et cetera, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we would just flirt with each other and so forth But I went to the shtibl myself.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I went to the Beit Yaakov school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I studied Chumash and Nach, and knew all my prayers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Some were very long, especially the one for the bathroom.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And learned from the fundamental-- learning from the fundamental of Judaism and its history, et cetera, et cetera, how we as a people were always chased, and chased, and chased, and chased.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And the chase has not stopped, because we are being chased today.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I would like to say this, that each and every time, when a person in the United States says this Holocaust never happened, it is like a dagger that goes right through all of us survivors.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "When we live day to day, we have put it in the subconscious so we can survive the conscious.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "But when you hitting our subconscious, we immediately are back 50 years ago when it happened.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "That means we are constantly sacrificing to relive our lives during the duress, and stress, and pain, and fear, and agonies, for survival that we went through in that war experience.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
